gallant-mast, where you stand upon two thin parallel sticks (almost peculiar to 
whalemen) called the t’ gallant cross-trees. Here, tossed about by the sea, 
the beginner feels about as cosy as he would standing on a bull’s horns. To 
be sure, in cold weather you may carry your house aloft with you, in the shape 
